{
  "texts": [
    "In contrast, there is potential for data leakage to an LLM through user queries (or prompts) as humans are the weakest link in security and privacy (Schneier, 2015).",
    "LLM service providers may use this interaction data for further model training and this may consequently spill the same sensitive data, that was once sent as a query, when attacked (Nasr et al., 2023).",
    "This risk is further exacerbated when employees of companies, in attempts to gain competitive edge, leak confidential company data through their prompts to an external LLM service such as Chat-GPT or Google Gemini.",
    "Despite the confidentiality guarantees provided by the LLM service providers, there have been unintentional instances where chat data was leaked (Open-AI, 2023).",
    "This concern has led some companies to enforce an organizational ban on chat models (Ray, 2023)."
  ]
}